# Copy to .env.local and fill in for ONE online backend (or neither, for
# solo + pass-and-play only). The app auto-selects: Azure wins if both are set.
# All values here are client-safe (they ship in the browser bundle).

# --- Option A: Azure (Functions + Table Storage) — see docs/AZURE.md ---
# The Function App base URL. Use "/api" when served same-origin behind Static
# Web Apps; otherwise the full host. `azd up` sets this for you in CI/build.
# VITE_API_BASE=https://YOUR-FUNC.azurewebsites.net/api

# --- Option B: Supabase (Edge Function + Postgres) — see docs/SUPABASE.md ---
# From Supabase → Project Settings → API. The publishable key is public (RLS-guarded).
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT-REF.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_KEY=sb_publishable_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
